parameters: Child B: "How can we become as strong as you, teacher?"
Kru: "Eh? Well... I'm not that strong, you know..."

Child A: "That's not true! My dad told me! He said you defeated nearly a
hundred monsters in an instant!"
Kru: "No... that story might have gotten a bit exaggerated..."
Kru: "Well... why do you want to become strong?"
Child B: "Is it... because we don't want to lose?"

Kru: "Hahaha! That's very honest of you! Such feelings are necessary to
become strong..."
Child B: "So we can become strong⁉"

Kru: "But that's not enough... If that's all you have, when you grow up and
face even tougher training, you might end up losing to yourself..."
Child A: "Then what should we do?"

Kru: "In my opinion... it's about whether you have something you truly want
to protect."
Child A: "Something we want to protect?"
Child B: "If we have that, we won't lose?"
Kru: "Well, not exactly. You might still lose sometimes..."

Kru: "But, it's most important to be able to overcome yourself. That's what
truly matters."
Child B: "Do you have something you want to protect, teacher?"
Child B: "Something you want to protect!"
Kru: "Well... yes, I do have things I want to protect, lots of them."
Kru: "That would be you students, I guess?"
Child B: "Not that kind of thing!"

Kru: "Eh! But it's the truth... Come on, hurry home or your dad will scold
you."

But... I know that no matter how much I train, there are things that just
can't be helped...
